<TITLE> Over 500 get bails extended by four months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 24 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Wednesday extended bails of over 500 people, including Khaleda Zia's son Tarique Rahman and former ministers Moudud Ahmed and Tariqul Islam, by four months. A vacation bench of Justice AKM Fazlur Rahman and Justice Sheikh Abdul Awal made the rulings in line with 515 appeals. The High Court had earlier granted them interim bails in separate cases. Former state minister Amanullah Aman, former energy adviser Mahmudur Rahman, former lawmakers Salahuddin Ahmed, Shahidul Islam, Joynal Abedin Faruque and Nasir Uddin Ahmed Pintu were also among the appellants. Barrister Mahbub Uddin Khokon, who stood for Moudud and Tarique in the court, told reporters that there was nothing wrong with the extension of bails for so many people together. "It is a regular job of the High Court," he said. b
